  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Atrial fibrillation and inflammation are strongly correlated. The aim of this study is to
      evaluate whether inflammation markers (alpha Defensin) predict maintenance of sinus rhythm
      following cardioversion. A secondary aim is to evaluate the role of Colchicine, an
      anti-inflammatory medication, in reducing the recurrence rate of atrial fibrillation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
